Once the dislocation geometry is set up, we can proceed with atomistic simulations. We use the Buckingham type pair potential from Lewis and Catlow
21 , which is a commonly used and reliable empirical potential for this material. Figure 1a shows the differential displacement map of the relaxed atomic coordinates through energy minimization. For the sake of clarity, only one of the two dislocations from the dipole is shown. The differential displacement map only indicates the displacement along the Burgers vector (along the dislocation line, or, in this case, the z direction). From Fig. 1a, the displacement of atoms in the core region of the screw dislocation is found to spread in the
